ğŸ”¹ find (File Search)
find is used to search for files/directories in a directory hierarchy based on conditions 
like name, size, type, modified time, etc.

ğŸ› ï¸ Syntax:

        find [path] [options]

ğŸ“Œ Common Options:

        -name â†’ Match by name

        -type â†’ File type (f for file, d for directory)

        -size â†’ Match by size

        -mtime â†’ Modified time

        -exec â†’ Run commands on found items

ğŸ§ª Examples:

        find . -name "*.txt"                  # Find all .txt files
        find /home -type d                   # Find directories
        find . -size +100M                   # Files larger than 100MB
        find . -mtime -7                     # Modified in the last 7 days
        find . -name "*.log" -exec rm {} \;  # Delete all .log files